name: Emma
meaning: Emma is an English name with roots in an old Germanic word meaning “whole” or “universal.” A perfect fit for the baby who will be your whole world!

name: Mia
meaning: Mia means 'Ocean Goddess' or 'Queen'; it can also mean 'guardian of justice'. It is derived from many names, most commonly from the name Maria, but is also derived from names like Amelia (and its various spellings), and Maya

name: Charlotte
meaning: The name Charlotte is girl's name of French origin meaning 'free man'.Charlotte is the feminine form of the male given name Charles. It derived from Charlot, a French diminutive of Charles meaning 'little Charles', and the name of Charlemagne’s son in French literature and legend.

name: Elizabeth
meaning: The name Elizabeth has religious roots and origins in Hebrew. Elizabeth can have several meanings including 'My God is an oath', 'My God is abundance', and 'edged to God'.

name: Abigail
meaning: Abigail means 'cause of joy' or 'father's joy' in Hebrew. In the Bible, Abigail is described as a beautiful and intelligent woman.

name: Marcy
meaning: The name Marcy is girl's name of Latin origin meaning 'Mars, god of war.'

name: Alessia
meaning: Alessia is an Italian given name, the feminine form of the male given name Alessio, the Italian form of Alexius. It is a popular name for females in Italy and was the second most popular name for Italian girls born in 2006

name: Thalita
meaning: The name Talitha is girl's name of Arabic, Aramaic origin meaning 'little girl'.

name: Aurora
meaning: Aurora is a mystical and romantic name that means 'dawn' in Latin. An aurora also refers to a natural light display in the Earth's sky called the aurora polaris, or polar lights, visible only in high-latitude regions like the North and South Poles.

name: Tamara
meaning: The name Tamara is primarily a female name of Russian origin that means Palm Tree.
